abstract: North Carolina  election supervisors on Friday added two candidates to the state's Republican presidential primary ballot, even though the state GOP had asked that Donald Trump be the only one listed.
snippet: North Carolina  election supervisors on Friday added two candidates to the state's Republican presidential primary ballot, even though the state GOP had asked that Donald Trump be the only one listed.
lead_paragraph: RALEIGH, N.C. — North Carolina election supervisors on Friday added two candidates to the state's Republican presidential primary ballot, even though the state GOP had asked that Donald Trump be the only one listed.
headline_main: Weld, Walsh Added to North Carolina GOP Primary Ballots
headline_print_headline: Weld, Walsh Added to North Carolina GOP Primary Ballots

abstract: Chinese leaders have long been sensitive about their communist country’s international image. Now, they are battling back — investing in diplomacy and a courtship of hearts and minds, just as the United States digs in on the Trump administration’s “America First” mindset.

lead_paragraph: GENEVA — Chinese leaders have long been sensitive about their communist country’s international image. Now, they are battling back — investing in diplomacy and a courtship of hearts and minds, just as the United States digs in on the Trump administration’s “America First” mindset.
headline_main: As Trump Shuns US Multilateralism, China Ups Diplomatic Ante

abstract: President Donald Trump will deliver the State of the Union to a joint session of Congress on Feb. 4.
snippet: President Donald Trump will deliver the State of the Union to a joint session of Congress on Feb. 4.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump will deliver the State of the Union to a joint session of Congress on Feb. 4.
headline_main: Pelosi Invites Trump to Deliver State of Union on Feb. 4
headline_print_headline: Pelosi Invites Trump to Deliver State of Union on Feb. 4

abstract: The invitation from Speaker Nancy Pelosi was notable because the president has lobbed insults at her in recent days for leading the House to approve two articles of impeachment.
snippet: The invitation from Speaker Nancy Pelosi was notable because the president has lobbed insults at her in recent days for leading the House to approve two articles of impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi invited President Trump to give the State of the Union address on Feb. 4, a sign that business is operating as usual in the nation’s capital, even after the House impeached the president two days ago.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-votin...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.

abstract: Readers in the United States with ties to Iran share how they have been affected by President Trump’s travel ban.
snippet: Readers in the United States with ties to Iran share how they have been affected by President Trump’s travel ban.
lead_paragraph: With the holidays and a long school break almost here and many families gathering together, we reached out to those who have been affected by President Trump’s travel ban to see how they and their relatives are managing.

abstract: Mexican officials expressed optimism Friday about the country’s economic future after the U.S. House of Representatives approved the renegotiated North American trade deal following lengthy and at times contentious negotiations.

lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Mexican officials expressed optimism Friday about the country’s economic future after the U.S. House of Representatives approved the renegotiated North American trade deal following lengthy and at times contentious negotiations.
